title: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes. JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) etc.
OB: The All types dialog shows obfuscated classes, such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd', etc.
EB: Obfuscated classes should be displayed with less prominence in the All types dialog.
SR: To reproduce the issue, open the All types dialog and observe obfuscated classes being displayed as prominent options.
